                            <comment id="15047379" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 20:01:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user StephanEwen commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1441#issuecomment-162997889&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1441#issuecomment-162997889&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Thanks for discovering and fixing this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Since that may happen with other projects as well, I was wondering if we should make this a dependency and managed dependency of the root flink project (from which all others inherit). Similar to slf4j, etc...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15047390" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 20:06:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user StephanEwen commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1441#issuecomment-163000184&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1441#issuecomment-163000184&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    As a separate issue: We could also look into updating our Kryo dependency:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    	&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;com.esotericsoftware&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
